    "plan_content": "Here's the plan summary:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**5 files total — 4 new, 1 modified (package.json files array only).**\n\n### Files\n\n| Action | Path |\n|---|---|\n| **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` |\n| **Modify** | `packages/next/package.json` (files array only) |\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n1. **Pattern mirrors `user-agent.ts` exactly** — `Geo` interface + `geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers)` (raw form) + `geo({ headers })` (request form), matching `userAgentFromString` / `userAgent`\n\n2. **`geo.js` mirrors `server.js`** — dual `module.exports = geoExports` + individual `exports.X = geoExports.X` for CommonJS/ESM named-import interop\n\n3. **`geo.d.ts` mirrors `server.d.ts`** — `export type { Geo }` + 4 function re-exports from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`\n\n4. **Header priority**: `x-vercel-ip-country` takes precedence over `cf-ipcountry` for `countryCode`; all 7 fields mapped from distinct headers\n\n5. **`country` full name**: derived via a 10-entry `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (AU, BR, CA, CN, DE, FR, GB, IN, JP, US); `undefined` for unknown codes\n\n6. **Haversine formula** for `geoDistance` — pure math, zero imports\n\n7. **`package.json` insertion**: `geo.js` / `geo.d.ts` inserted after `form.d.ts` (alphabetical g after f)\n\n8. **Tests**: `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` only — 9 assertions across 4 describe blocks covering all exported functions",
